<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692481>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 49–54. External (49, 51, 53) and internal (50, 52, 54) female genitalia of Podisus ventralis (49–50), Podisus graziae sp. n. (51–52), and Podisus thomasi sp. n. (53–54). Abbreviations: ar, arcus; cs, capsula seminalis; da, distal annular crest; id, inner duct; la9, laterotergites IX; md, median duct; od, outer duct; pa, proximal annular crest; pi, pars intermedialis; rs, ring sclerites; tvi, thickening of vaginal intima; tva 9, thickening of valvulae IX; va, vesicular area; vf8, valvifers VIII; vf9, valvifers IX; X, segment X. Scale bars: 49, 51, 53 = 0.5 mm; 50, 52, 54 = 0.1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4692481/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692477>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 34–39. Male right parameres (34, 36, 38) and right pseudoclaspers (35, 37, 39) of Podisus ventralis (34–35), Podisus graziae sp. n. (36–37), and Podisus thomasi sp. n. (38–39). Abbreviations: im, inner margin; om, outer margin. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4692477/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692471>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 1–15. Type specimens examined, in ventral and dorsal views, with their respective labels. 1–3, Arma ventralis (NH- MUK); 4–6, Arma pallipes (NHMUK); 7–9, Podisus neniator (SDEI); 10–12; Podisus graziae sp. n. (MZSP); 13–15, Podisus thomasi sp. n. (NHMUK). 7–9, photographed by Angelika Weirauch (Senckenberg Deutsches Entomologisches Institut); original photos cropped, light levels and contrast adjusted. Scale bars = 4 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4692471/files/figure.png" .

